TY  - JOUR
T1  - Preferential Trading Theory: The n Commodity Case
AU  - Berglas, Eitan
Y1  - 1979/04/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260758
DO  - 10.1086/260758
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 315
EP  - 331
VL  - 87
IS  - 2
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This is a general equilibrium analysis of preferential trading. A method was developed which allows the analysis of the many-good case and which suggests the tools for empirical studies. It is shown that increasing the number of commodities beyond two introduces new considerations. It is, however, always possible to identify welfare-increasing tariff changes. The study analyzes the inter-relationship between preferential trading and a unilateral movement to free trade. The effect of a customs union on income distribution among union members is emphasized.
AB  - This is a general equilibrium analysis of preferential trading. A method was developed which allows the analysis of the many-good case and which suggests the tools for empirical studies. It is shown that increasing the number of commodities beyond two introduces new considerations. It is, however, always possible to identify welfare-increasing tariff changes. The study analyzes the inter-relationship between preferential trading and a unilateral movement to free trade. The effect of a customs union on income distribution among union members is emphasized.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260758
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260758
Y2  - 2024/03/22
